  "body": "Hi!\r\n\r\nIn commit 13b5cd2f19dd0ca69f89b2d04eb7d00e9c45898d, the validator for the slot param in `getStorageAt` was changed from `rpcQuantity` to `rpcStorageSlot`. The main difference is that the first disallows hex 0 padding and the second requires it.\r\n\r\nHowever, the `setStorageAt` method continues to use `rpcQuantity` for this field: https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/f23d106048c2cd5d98bcb3e11596afbcb085afa8/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/hardhat.ts#L309\r\n\r\nThis means that a user who is reading from and writing to a slot has to make sure to pad zeros when reading and strip zeros when writing, which seems inconsistent and is generally a pain.\r\n\r\nShouldn't `setStorageAt` be changed to use the `rpcStorageSlot` validation on its slot parameter, for consistency with `getStorageAt`?",
  "closed_by": null,
